-- pipeline.fl — Multi-model orchestration pipeline demo
-- Demonstrates: model aliases, parallel execution, conditionals, functions

-- Define specialist model aliases
Define model fast_model as groq/llama-3.3-70b-versatile with temperature 0, max_tokens 100.
Define model smart_model as claude with temperature 0.3, max_tokens 500.

-- Sample data
Let articles be a list containing
    "Artificial intelligence has made significant progress in healthcare diagnostics.",
    "New research shows climate change accelerating faster than previous models predicted.",
    "Tech stocks fell sharply as investors worried about interest rate increases.".

Output "=== Multi-Model Pipeline Demo ===".
Output "".
Output "Step 1: Fast classification (Groq Llama)".

-- Step 1: Classify all articles in parallel using a fast cheap model
In parallel, for each article in articles:
    @model(temperature: 0, max_tokens: 5)
    Ask fast_model to "Classify into one word: tech, health, climate, finance, or other." using text article and call the result article_topic.
End parallel loop.

Output "Step 2: Summarise each article (Claude)".

-- Step 2: Summarise each article
For each article in articles:
    @model(temperature: 0.3, max_tokens: 80)
    Ask smart_model to "Summarise in one sentence." using text article and call the result article_summary.
    Output article_summary.
End loop.

Output "".
Output "Pipeline complete.".
